HEADWORD: Delacrymation
<hw>De*lac`ry*ma"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>delacrimatio</ets>, fr. <ets>delacrimare</ets> to weep. See
<er>Lachrymation</er>.]</ety> <def>An involuntary discharge of watery
humors from the eyes; wateriness of the eyes.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bailey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

